The emergency medicine practice cycle is focused on primary assessment and treatment of acutely ill or injured patients in emergency department. Students will learn about the organisation of emergency medicine, triage and obtain practical skills for initial management of emergency patient. 
At least 100 corresponding AMBOSS platform cases must be solved during the emergency medicine cycle, the completion will be checked up on at the end of the semester.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of emergency medicine practice cycle is to provide a clinical experience in emergency department: organisation of emergency medicine, incl. patient triage principles, the recognition, differential diagnosis and primary treatment of acutely ill or injured patient, incl. major trauma.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the emergency medicine cycle the Student: - knows the organisation of emergency medicine and is able to perform triage in emergency department - is able to contact with the patient and to collect disease history, is able to perform objective examination of the patient and to assess the results of investigation or analysis - is able to perform basic medical manipulations and investigations according to recommendation of clinical practice logbook - knows the primary management of a patient in critical condition (cardiac arrest, major trauma, life-threatening arrhythmias, acute coronary syndrome, acute respiratory failure, acute renal failure, coma and shock) - knows how to complete medial documentation in emergency department
